<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-21T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-21T12:00:00-05:00" n="610" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d610">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23 Repatriates/1: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-21T12:00:00-05:00">February 21,
                                1933—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>38. Your 93, February 20, 5 p.m., repeated to Legation at Bogotá with
                            instructions to take matter up with the Colombian Government and advise
                            you directly.<note n="4" xml:id="d610fn4">Telegram No. 33, February 21,
                                11 a.m., to the Minister in Colombia, not printed.</note> You may
                            communicate directly with Legation at Bogotá regarding arrangements for
                            repatriation of Colombians.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>